---
description: Use StrEnum for closed string sets in Python (not raw literals)
alwaysApply: true
---

# Closed sets use StrEnum

When a value is drawn from a **fixed, known set** of strings (API enums, device families, rule triggers, action types), define a `StrEnum` in `app/` (typically `app/device_enums.py` or a domain module) and compare against enum members — not bare string literals.

```python
# Good
from app.device_enums import RuleTrigger

if rule.trigger == RuleTrigger.EDGE_TRUE:
    ...

# Avoid in library code
if rule.trigger == "edge_true":
    ...
```

Pydantic models may use the enum as the field type; JSON wire values stay the same (`"edge_true"`, etc.).

**Exceptions:** one-off user-facing error messages, test fixture JSON dicts, and third-party literals required for interoperability.
